So far, this marriage was better
than my last one.

14:40.447 --> 14:44.484
My wife cooked,
and at least one of my kids
was a blood relation to me.

14:52.692 --> 14:56.163
And compared to all the sirens
and the loud hooker fights
at the motel,

14:56.229 --> 14:58.398
livin' here was peaceful
and homey.

14:58.465 --> 15:01.634
And we actually
spent time together
like a real family.

15:08.641 --> 15:12.379
And I found it was easier
puttin' these boys to bed
than my last two.

15:12.445 --> 15:16.783
Mainly 'cause these boys
drank themselves to sleep
before story time.

15:16.849 --> 15:21.188
And I know it might sound crazy,
but as far as
forced marriages go,

15:21.254 --> 15:23.490
this one was turnin' out
pretty nice.

15:23.556 --> 15:27.194
I guess bein' married to
Ralph's mom was somethin'
I could get used to.

15:27.260 --> 15:29.997
And at least I could have
if not for one thing.

15:30.063 --> 15:34.334
I had a new older wife
who expected me to fulfill
my husbandly duties.

15:34.401 --> 15:38.371
Sorry.
Uh, I just ate a big meal.
M-My doctor says, uh,

15:38.438 --> 15:41.941
I have to wait at least
three hours before swimmin'
or humpin',

15:42.009 --> 15:45.578
so don't wait up.

15:45.645 --> 15:48.181
[ Earl Narrating ]
And every night that week,
after the boys went to bed,

15:48.248 --> 15:51.051
I came up with a new way
to avoid my husbandly duties.

15:51.118 --> 15:53.653
There's a bunch of birds
unfairly attackin' a squirrel
on the lawn.

15:53.720 --> 15:56.923
- I gotta get involved.
- [ Door Closes ]

15:56.990 --> 15:59.759
Don't wait up.

15:59.826 --> 16:02.762
The string
came out of my sweatpants.
It's gonna be an all-nighter.

16:02.829 --> 16:05.332
The Chinese are on the march.
I'm on hold with Mike
from Bombay.

16:05.398 --> 16:07.134
He's tryin' to walk me
through the new toaster.

16:07.200 --> 16:08.901
Randy got out.
Gotta go find him.

16:08.968 --> 16:12.705
I have to drive three counties
over to get some rubbers.
I'm an odd size.

16:15.608 --> 16:18.378
[ Snores ]
Hey.

16:18.445 --> 16:21.581
- What in the hell's
wrong with you?
- Nothin'.

16:22.815 --> 16:25.552
I mean, I got a little bit
of a crick in my neck, but--

16:25.618 --> 16:28.521
Yeah, well, my mom told me
you ain't consummated
your holy matrimony yet,

16:28.588 --> 16:30.723
so I'm gonna ask you again,
what the hell's wrong with you?

16:30.790 --> 16:34.161
Ralph, look,
makin' an honest woman
out of your mom was easy,

16:34.227 --> 16:37.097
but the consummatin' part
may be a hurdle I can't jump.

16:37.164 --> 16:41.101
- So, what are you sayin'?
My mom's not foxy?
- No, your mom's foxy.

16:41.168 --> 16:43.636
But you have to admit,
she's also--

16:43.703 --> 16:48.641
An angel?
A female angel?
With female needs.

16:48.708 --> 16:52.445
Now, look, I know
this is gonna sound crazy,
given where we started and all,

16:52.512 --> 16:55.348
but if you don't
sleep with my mom,

16:55.415 --> 16:57.484
I think I'm gonna
have to kill you.

17:00.487 --> 17:04.357
[ Sighs ]
Fine. I'll do it tonight
after the show.

17:04.424 --> 17:07.294
But once I consummate your mom,
I'm officially your stepdad,

17:07.360 --> 17:11.831
and I won't stand for
any more threats on my life.
Done.

17:11.898 --> 17:13.666
[ Earl Narrating ]
So that was it.

17:13.733 --> 17:16.269
And unlike the last time
Phish Tahko played,

17:16.336 --> 17:21.374
I wasn't thinkin' about how nice
it was gonna be to have sex
with the girl in the front row.

17:24.043 --> 17:27.780
All right, let's get ready to
tear the roof off this mother!

17:27.847 --> 17:30.850
Not really, though.
Please, stay off the roof.

17:30.917 --> 17:33.052
Phish Tahko!

17:38.891 --> 17:42.129
** [ "Frankenstein" ]

17:55.041 --> 17:59.246
Tom, the way you sang tonight,
buddy, I'm definitely
comin' to your funeral.

17:59.312 --> 18:01.148
[ Earl Narrating ]
We put on a great show.

18:01.214 --> 18:05.118
- But I wasn't lookin' forward
to my next performance.
- Excuse me.

18:05.185 --> 18:07.954
[ Earl Narrating ]
Since bein' drunk helped me
through this the first time,

18:08.020 --> 18:12.159
I decided I'd better be
twice as drunk this time.
Crabman, shot of whiskey.

18:14.894 --> 18:19.332
[ Man ]
* I am drowning in
a whiskey river *

18:20.533 --> 18:24.036
* Bathing my memory'd mind *

18:24.103 --> 18:26.839
Crabman, another shot.
* In the wetness of its soul *

18:28.808 --> 18:34.581
* Feeling the amber current
flowin' from my mind *

18:34.647 --> 18:39.018
Crabman, three more shots.
You know what?
Just-Just leave the bottle.

18:39.085 --> 18:42.121
* Empty heart you left so cold *

18:42.189 --> 18:47.727
* Whiskey river
take my mind *

18:47.794 --> 18:52.465
* Don't let her memory
torture me **

18:54.301 --> 18:56.303
[ Body Thuds ]
[ Bottle Clatters ]

19:01.474 --> 19:03.410
Earl.

19:03.476 --> 19:06.613
Earl.
Did I do it?

19:06.679 --> 19:10.250
Is it over?
Did I consummate my marriage?

19:10.317 --> 19:14.687
No. But you did try to
consummate that bar stool.
I just left you two alone.

19:16.923 --> 19:19.426
See you, Earl.
See you, Earl.

19:20.860 --> 19:23.496
[ Earl Narrating ]
The worst part of
the two-mile walk home...

19:23.563 --> 19:25.865
was that it
sobered me up a little.

19:27.534 --> 19:30.136
But I was still determined
to make love to my new wife.

19:30.203 --> 19:32.171
The thing was--
[ Gasps ]

19:34.341 --> 19:36.343
Tom had beat me to it.

19:36.409 --> 19:38.545
Funny thing about
bein' in a band is...

19:38.611 --> 19:41.281
no matter how young
and good-looking
the bass player is,

19:41.348 --> 19:44.251
chicks always dig
the lead singer.

19:47.720 --> 19:51.924
So while I was workin' hard
to lose my grip on reality,

19:51.991 --> 19:56.663
Tom was gettin' a pretty good
grip on Lorraine.

19:56.729 --> 20:00.267
It was clear that
me and Ralph's mom
didn't belong together.

20:00.333 --> 20:04.437
So after the annulment,
her and Tom continued
seeing each other.

20:04.504 --> 20:08.641
And Ralph was no longer mad
at me, since I'd made an honest
woman out of his mom.

20:08.708 --> 20:11.378
And Tom was more than
just her new boyfriend.

20:11.444 --> 20:13.546
He was the father figure
that Ralph never had.

20:15.948 --> 20:18.385
And that made everybody happy.

